<title>ZAIRE: Zaire sets tough conditions as U.N. envoy arrives.</title>
<headline>Zaire sets tough conditions as U.N. envoy arrives.</headline>
<dateline>KINSHASA 1996-11-08</dateline>
<text>
<p>Zaire stated categorically that it would no longer allow Rwandan and Burundian refugees on its soil as a U.N. envoy arrived on Friday for talks on urgent relief for over a million refugees displaced by fighting.</p>
<p>&quot;No new refugee camps can be built anywhere in Zaire,&quot; Information Minister Boguo Makeli declared on television, reading from decisions of a cabinet meeting. The existing camps have been abandonned.</p>
</text>
